descript.abstract: Data from a number of sources is used for the development and ongoing maintenance of the MajorRoads feature class. Source data includes SanGIS Roads_All, Caltrans State Highway Centerlines, and street centerline data from the County of Imperial. Regional aerial imagery (1'/pixel resolution or better) is generally used as a guide for delineating roadway alignments, primarily using heads up digitizing methods, using ArcGIS desktop software.
descript.purpose: The MajorRoads feature class includes major arterials and state highway features for the San Diego and Imperial County region, as well as additional features for portions of Orange and Riverside Counties and northern Baja, CA. The data was developed primarily for use in developing cartographic products and services at the regional or sub-regional scale.
descript.supplinf:
SOURCE: SanGIS centerline road file; General Plan circulation elements of the local jurisdictions in the San Diego region; Caltrans State highway inventory (FUNC coverage); SANDAG Regional Transportation Improvement Program and Regional Transportation Plan.
The SANDAG transportation database is constantly updated to reflect the latest transportation improvements and plans for the San Diego region. New major-road and freeway layers will be produced when significant changes are made to SANDAG's transportation database. This layer contains existing freeways in addition to the major roads.

overview.eaover: This dataset is a spatial representation of the system of major roadway facilities for the San Diego County region. The dataset also includes major roads for Imperial County, Northern Baja California, and portions of Orange and Riverside Counties. Significant attribute fields in this dataset are NM, SD, StateHwy, HOV and Toll. Review attribute information below for more information.
